# Backend

## Where logic lives

| Concern | File |
|---------|------|
| Server boot, Express, Socket.IO, cron stack push | `backend/dockge-server.ts` |
| Stack FS + compose lifecycle | `backend/stack.ts` |
| PTY terminals | `backend/terminal.ts` |
| Auth / settings / composerize | `backend/socket-handlers/main-socket-handler.ts` |
| Agent routing (`agent` envelope) | `backend/socket-handlers/agent-proxy-socket-handler.ts` |
| Add/remove/update agents | `backend/socket-handlers/manage-agent-socket-handler.ts` |
| Deploy/start/stop/… stacks | `backend/agent-socket-handlers/docker-socket-handler.ts` |
| Terminal join/input/resize | `backend/agent-socket-handlers/terminal-socket-handler.ts` |
| Remote agent clients | `backend/agent-manager.ts` |
| Status enums / compose names | `common/util-common.ts` |

## Patterns

- Extend `SocketHandler` (direct events) or `AgentSocketHandler` (via `agent` proxy). Do **not** invent REST endpoints for app logic.
- Gate privileged events with `checkLogin(socket)`. Callbacks: `{ ok, msg, msgi18n?, … }` via `callbackResult` / `callbackError`.
- Persist compose under `stacksDir/<name>/` (name: `/^[a-z0-9_-]+$/`). Never store stack YAML only in SQLite.
- Stack status: `UNKNOWN=0`, `CREATED_FILE=1`, `CREATED_STACK=2`, `RUNNING=3`, `EXITED=4`.
- Migrations: Knex TS under `backend/migrations/`. ORM: RedBean Node. MySQL is typed but unimplemented.

## Agent socket events (via `agent`)

`deployStack`, `saveStack`, `deleteStack`, `getStack`, `requestStackList`, `startStack`, `stopStack`, `restartStack`, `updateStack`, `downStack`, `serviceStatusList`, `dockerStats`, service start/stop/restart, terminals (`terminalInput`, `terminalJoin`, `interactiveTerminal`, …).
